snippet: Members of the long-repressed pro-democracy party of Daw Aung San Suu Kyi gathered in Yangon for their first party congress, in an attempt to revitalize the group.
abstract: Members of long-repressed pro-democracy party of Daw Aung San Suu Kyi gather in Yangon, Myanmar, for their first party congress, in attempt to revitalize the group nearly quarter century after it was founded.
lead_paragraph: Members of the long-repressed pro-democracy party of Daw Aung San Suu Kyi gathered in Yangon for their first party congress, in an attempt to revitalize the group.

headline.seo: In Myanmar, Pro-Democracy Party Meets for First Time
headline.main: In Myanmar, Pro-Democracy Party Meets in Bid to Revitalize
headline.print_headline: In Myanmar, Pro-Democracy Party Meets in Bid to Revitalize
